---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CallToAction from "@/components/CallToAction.astro";
import { site } from "@/config/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Dominic 'Dom' Conte - legal-tech founder, former real-estate solicitor, and co-founder of Purple. The story of moving from practising law to building AI products lawyers actually use."
  path="/about/"
>
  <section class="container-content pt-16 sm:pt-24">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr] lg:gap-16">
      <!-- Bio -->
      <div>
        <p class="label mb-4">About</p>
        <h1 class="text-display-sm">From practising law to building it.</h1>

        <div class="prose-editorial mt-10">
          <p>
            I'm Dominic "Dom" Conte - a legal-tech founder and former
            real-estate solicitor. Today I'm {site.jobTitle.toLowerCase()} at
            <a href={site.company.url} rel="noopener" target="_blank"
              >{site.company.name}</a
            >, where we build AI products for law firms, and I write and speak
            about what it actually takes to make legal innovation stick.
          </p>
          <p>
            I didn't start in technology. I trained and practised as a
            real-estate solicitor, which is where I learned the thing that still
            drives the work: the gap between how legal services are sold and how
            the work actually gets done. Lawyers are surrounded by repetitive,
            high-stakes tasks that software should have solved years ago - and
            yet most of the tools aimed at them go unused.
          </p>
          <p>
            That gap is what pulled me out of practice and into building. I
            wanted to make tools that fee-earners reach for because they're
            genuinely better, not because they've been told to. Practising law
            first turned out to be the unfair advantage: I know where the work
            is painful, where the judgement really lives, and why so many
            "obvious" products quietly fail to land.
          </p>

          <h2>What I care about</h2>
          <p>
            Adoption over hype. The hard part of legal AI was never the model -
            it's changing what people actually do on a Tuesday afternoon. I care
            about narrow, real use cases; keeping a human in the loop where
            judgement matters; and being honest about what works and what
            doesn't.
          </p>

          <h2>Beyond the work</h2>
          <p>
            I'm based in {site.location}. When I'm not building, I'm usually
            writing about legal innovation, on a podcast, or on a stage talking
            about how regulated professions adopt new technology. If any of that
            overlaps with what you're working on, I'd love to hear from you.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            The technology is no longer the hard part. The hard part is the same
            as it has always been in professional services - changing what
            people actually do.
          </blockquote>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="lg:pt-16">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-hairline bg-paper">
          <img
            src={site.headshot}
            alt={`${site.name} - ${site.jobTitle} at ${site.company.name}`}
            width="640"
            height="800"
            class="aspect-[4/5] w-full object-cover"
            loading="eager"
          />
        </div>

        <dl class="mt-8 space-y-5">
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Role</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">{site.jobTitle}, {site.company.name}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Based in</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">{site.location}</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-1">Focus</dt>
            <dd class="text-ink">Legal AI, product, adoption</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="label mb-2">Find me</dt>
            <dd class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
              <a href={site.socials.linkedin} rel="me noopener" target="_blank"
                >LinkedIn</a
              >
              <a href={site.socials.x} rel="me noopener" target="_blank">X</a>
              <a href={site.socials.github} rel="me noopener" target="_blank"
                >GitHub</a
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Let's talk"
    body="Whether it's a speaking invitation, a collaboration, or a question about legal AI - my inbox is open."
    primaryHref="/contact/"
    primaryLabel="Get in touch"
    secondaryHref="/writing/"
    secondaryLabel="Read my writing"
  />
</BaseLayout>
